525
00:34:36,532 --> 00:34:39,766
相对于你和你的队员们来说
My life will be a small price to pay

526
00:34:39,767 --> 00:34:43,083
我这条小命算不了什么
for the lives of you and your team.

527
00:34:46,927 --> 00:34:49,223
那如果我们炸掉这整个设施呢?
Then how about the destruction of this facility?

528
00:34:49,973 --> 00:34:52,106
是不是也算不了什么?
Is that a small enough price as well?

529
00:34:52,305 --> 00:34:54,052
你骗人
You lie.

530
00:34:54,053 --> 00:34:56,606
我告诉过他们 把炸药埋在哪里
可以发挥最大威力
I told them where to hide the charges for maximum effect,

531
00:34:56,735 --> 00:34:59,606
足以炸掉这整个设施
包括所有研究成果
enough explosives to destroy this place and all of its research.

532
00:34:59,712 --> 00:35:02,477
所有你们取得的领先成果
Any advantage your hive may hold over its rivals

533
00:35:02,478 --> 00:35:04,868
在我按下这个按钮后
就都将灰飞烟灭
will be gone with the push of a button.

534
00:35:08,548 --> 00:35:09,790
等等!
Wait!

535
00:35:22,691 --> 00:35:24,753
跟他们说 放我们过去
Tell them to let us through.

536
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:29,605
怎么保证你们跑远后 不会按下那个按钮
What's to stop you from triggering the explosives from a safe distance?

537
00:35:29,699 --> 00:35:31,738
我留下
My presence here.

538
00:35:35,992 --> 00:35:38,417
放他们走 我留下
You let them go. I'll remain behind.

539
00:35:38,453 --> 00:35:40,855
- Tyre...
- 等他们到星门那里后
- Tyre...
- once they've reached the gate,

540
00:35:40,856 --> 00:35:44,295
我会用这个装置
来换取我自己的自由
I'll trade you this device for my freedom.

541
00:35:46,193 --> 00:35:48,408
再不走我们就都会死在这里
Or we all die together.

542
00:35:53,118 --> 00:35:55,039
放他们走
Let them go.

543
00:36:09,286 --> 00:36:11,478
我稍后就会跟上
I'll be right behind you.

544
00:36:17,052 --> 00:36:18,446
我们走
Let's go.

545
00:36:43,905 --> 00:36:47,398
你这样做等于是放弃了一份
难以想象的大礼
You turn your back on an incredible gift.

546
00:36:47,667 --> 00:36:50,632
事实上 是你首先抛弃我的
Actually, you turned your back on me first.

547
00:36:51,030 --> 00:36:52,788
我还没好好感谢你呢
And I thank you for it.

548
00:36:52,941 --> 00:36:54,534
我们出来了
We're clear.

549
00:36:55,062 --> 00:36:58,167
我可以宽恕你
You're not beyond forgiveness.

550
00:36:58,718 --> 00:37:01,050
现在还不是太晚
It's not too late for you.

551
00:37:01,273 --> 00:37:03,066
不 已经太迟了...
Yes, it is...

552
00:37:03,312 --> 00:37:05,468
对我们双方而言
for both of us.

553
00:37:25,637 --> 00:37:28,309
恢复周期大概需要多长?
What kind of a timeframe for recovery are we looking at?

554
00:37:28,310 --> 00:37:30,453
很难估计
It's impossible to predict.

555
00:37:30,571 --> 00:37:34,766
他体内的酶素太多
几乎超过了机体能承受的极限
He has so much of the enzyme running through him that his body can hardly process it.

556
00:37:35,750 --> 00:37:37,555
在机体代谢完这些酶后
When it eventually does,

557
00:37:37,696 --> 00:37:39,594
他就会安静下来
that's when he'll come down,

558
00:37:40,063 --> 00:37:41,996
而这是个艰巨的过程
and he'll come down hard.

559
00:37:42,172 --> 00:37:44,375
我要去跟他谈谈
I'm going to talk to him.

560
00:37:49,002 --> 00:37:50,373
打开
Open it.

561
00:37:54,408 --> 00:37:56,072
看谁来了
There he is.

562
00:37:57,900 --> 00:37:59,213
嘿 伙计
Hey, buddy.

563
00:37:59,646 --> 00:38:01,123
伙计
Buddy.

564
00:38:01,228 --> 00:38:04,849
你还准备把我关多久?
So, how long are you planning on keeping me prisoner?

565
00:38:04,896 --> 00:38:07,017
在你头脑彻底清醒之后
As long as it takes to clear your head.

566
00:38:07,018 --> 00:38:08,260
我的头脑很清醒
My head is clear.

567
00:38:08,261 --> 00:38:10,826
你现在可能感觉很好 不过
Well, you may be feeling fine right now, but

568
00:38:10,978 --> 00:38:13,556
这一过程对你来说可能会非常痛苦
things are going to get pretty rough for you.

569
00:38:13,709 --> 00:38:16,017
我们会一直陪伴你的
We're going to get you through this.

570
00:38:16,580 --> 00:38:18,947
不管你打的是什么主意
都不会奏效的
Whatever you've got planned, it's not going to work.

571
00:38:19,252 --> 00:38:20,658
你有两个选择
You've got a choice--

572
00:38:20,834 --> 00:38:23,705
要么杀了我 要么就放我走
you'd better kill me or you let me go.

573
00:38:23,963 --> 00:38:28,814
如果放我走 我保证不会再来
找你和Atlantis的麻烦
And if you let me go, I promise I won't come after you or atlantis.

574
00:38:29,306 --> 00:38:30,842
跟Tyre说 我也不会去找他的麻烦
Tell tyre I won't come after him either.

575
00:38:30,900 --> 00:38:33,338
Tyre死了
Tyre's dead.

576
00:38:34,263 --> 00:38:37,099
他牺牲了自己 炸掉了Wraith的实验室
He sacrificed himself taking out the wraith lab.

577
00:38:38,517 --> 00:38:39,560
这个叛徒
Yeah, well, he was a traitor.

578
00:38:39,619 --> 00:38:41,529
不 他是我们的好朋友
No, he was a good friend.

579
00:38:41,974 --> 00:38:43,650
我们都是好朋友
We all are.

580
00:38:45,884 --> 00:38:48,052
你很快就会意识到这一点的
You're going to realize that pretty soon.

581
00:38:48,486 --> 00:38:50,267
嘿 你要么杀了我 要么就放我走
Hey, will you just kill me or set me free.

582
00:38:50,268 --> 00:38:51,919
Sheppard!
Sheppard!

583
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:53,982
杀了我 或者放我走!
You kill me or set me free!

584
00:38:54,275 --> 00:38:56,513
Sheppard!
Sheppard!

585
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:09,024
杀了我吧!
Kill me please!

586
00:39:09,025 --> 00:39:11,590
求你们了!
Please kill me!

587
00:39:11,941 --> 00:39:13,430
不!
No!

588
00:39:44,909 --> 00:39:48,355
我拥有他们所称之为的钢琴指
纤细 灵巧
I had what they called piano fingers-- slim, nimble.

589
00:39:48,425 --> 00:39:51,331
难怪我父母给我报了钢琴课
It's really no surprise that my parents signed me up for lessons.

590
00:39:51,332 --> 00:39:54,210
我的首任老师 跟往常一样
向我打招呼
My first teacher, of course, hailed me as a natural.

591
00:39:54,211 --> 00:39:57,034
一个俄国女人 忘了她是叫
普兰斯基还是巴兰斯基
Big russian woman, polanskii or baranski or...

592
00:39:57,035 --> 00:39:57,901
Sheppard...
sheppard...

593
00:39:57,948 --> 00:39:59,518
反正是个什么"斯基"
definitely a "ski".

594
00:40:01,557 --> 00:40:03,409
Ronon?
Ronon?

595
00:40:03,784 --> 00:40:06,983
感觉怎样?
Hey, uh, how do you feel?

596
00:40:09,889 --> 00:40:12,057
感觉想打人
Like hitting someone.

597
00:40:13,464 --> 00:40:15,139
选好对象了没?
Anyone in particular?

598
00:40:16,815 --> 00:40:20,003
你 如果你不给我松绑
并给我带点吃的过来的话
You, if you don't loosen these straps and get me something to eat.

599
00:40:20,659 --> 00:40:22,018
这是个好兆头
That is a good sign.

600
00:40:22,124 --> 00:40:23,202
这是个好兆头!
That's a good sign!

601
00:40:24,268 --> 00:40:26,741
他好了! 他好了!
He's back! He's back!

602
00:40:27,819 --> 00:40:29,717
这么说他已经完全恢复了?
So he's fully recovered?

603
00:40:30,128 --> 00:40:32,307
他的身体仍很虚弱
Well, physically he's still weak,

604
00:40:32,308 --> 00:40:36,212
不过血液检查显示 他体内
已经没有酶素了
but his bloodwork shows no traces of the enzyme in his system, so

605
00:40:36,458 --> 00:40:39,915
不用多久 他就能恢复原样
he should be back to his old self in no time.

606
00:40:40,173 --> 00:40:41,450
真是好消息
Good to hear.

607
00:40:41,767 --> 00:40:42,857
好了 很晚了
Well, it's late.

608
00:40:42,997 --> 00:40:46,337
我要回房间 换一身休闲一点的衣服
I think I'll head back to my quarters and change into something a little more relaxed.

609
00:40:46,513 --> 00:40:47,814
晚安
Good night.

610
00:40:51,881 --> 00:40:54,400
John 能和你谈谈么?
John, may I have a word?

611
00:40:54,740 --> 00:40:56,627
当然
Yeah. Sure.

612
00:41:03,334 --> 00:41:05,232
Teyla 请进
Teyla. Come in.

613
00:41:08,596 --> 00:41:12,850
你不是说过换一身休闲一点的衣服
I thought you said you were changing into something more relaxed.

614
00:41:14,151 --> 00:41:16,401
对我来说 这就是休闲服
For me, this is more relaxed.

615
00:41:16,635 --> 00:41:18,874
- 想来一杯么?
- 不 谢了
- Can I offer you a drink?
- No, thank you.

616
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:22,524
我和John谈过了
现在想获得正式的批准
I just spoke with john, and now I would like to make it official.

617
00:41:23,056 --> 00:41:25,259
希望能让我立即归队
I'm requesting a return to active duty.

618
00:41:25,317 --> 00:41:28,798
回到Sheppard中校所在小队中的位置
I would like to resume my position on colonel sheppard's team.

619
00:41:29,173 --> 00:41:30,884
你确信要这么做?
You're sure this is what you want?

620
00:41:31,341 --> 00:41:32,513
非常希望
Very much so.

621
00:41:32,888 --> 00:41:35,079
那好吧 欢迎归队
Well, then, welcome back.

622
00:41:35,559 --> 00:41:37,341
谢谢 Woolsey先生
Thank you, mr. Woolsey.

623
00:41:37,528 --> 00:41:39,110
- 晚安
- 晚安
- Good night.
- Good night.

